    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="235" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <head>No. 180.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Daggett</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Honolulu</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-09-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 24, 1882</date>.
                            (Received October 11.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that Hon. John
                        Makini Kapena, postmaster-general of the Hawaiian Kingdom, has been
                        appointed envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary to the court of
                        Japan, and will proceed thence at once by way of San Francisco.</p>
                <p>The avowed purpose of his mission is to arrange for bringing Japanese
                        laborers and their families to these islands—a project approved by the sugar
                        planters’ union.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROLLIN M. DAGGETT.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
